                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d292">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/7642: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-15T15:00:00+03:00"
                            >January 15, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 15—1:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>77. The Rumanian Minister told me last night that the Rumanian railroad
                    authorities had been directed by the German authorities to reserve 1500 special
                    trains during January for the transport of German troops and equipment. He gave
                    it as his opinion the size of the army Germany is concentrating in Rumania is
                    very much greater than could conceivably be required for an invasion of Bulgaria
                    and Greece.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
